1. A manufacturing method of a non-oriented electrical steel sheet, comprising:

performing hot-rolling of a steel material so as to form a steel strip, the steel material containing, in mass%:

Si: not less than 0.1% nor more than 4.0%;

Al: not less than 0.1% nor more than 3.0%; and

Mn: not less than 0.1% nor more than 2.0%;

a C content being 0.003% or less, and a balance being composed of Fe and inevitable impurity elements;

next, performing first cold-rolling of the steel strip;

next, performing intermediate annealing of the steel strip;

next, performing second cold-rolling of the steel strip; and next, performing finish annealing of the steel strip, wherein

a finish temperature in the hot-rolling is 900°C or less, the first cold-rolling is started without performing annealing after the hot-rolling; and a rolling reduction in the second cold-rolling is not less than 40% nor more than 85%.

7. A method of producing a hot-dipped steel, comprising:

preparing a hot-dip plating bath containing an alloy composition containing,

25% to 75% by weight of Al, 0.1% to 10% by weight of Mg, 0.02% to 1.0% by weight of Cr, 0.5% to 10% by weight, based on Al, of Si, 1 ppm to 1000 ppm by weight of Sr, 0.1% to 1.0% by weight of Fe, the remainder being Zn,

the weight ratio of Si to Mg being 100:50 to 100:300;

wherein, optionally, said plating bath contains one or several components selected from alkaline earth elements, Sc, Y, lanthanoid elements, Ti and B, and wherein the total content of the alkaline earth elements, Sc, Y and lanthanoid elements, if present, in the hot-dip plating bath as a weight ratio is 1.0% or less, and wherein, optionally, said plating bath contains unavoidable impurities such as Pb, Cd, Cu or Mn, wherein the total content of these unavoidable impurities, if present, as a weight ratio based on the weight of the hot-dip plating bath is 1% by the weight or less;

passing a steel substrate through said hot-dip plating bath to deposit a hot-dip plating metal on a surface thereof; and solidifying said hot-dip plating metal to form an aluminum-zinc alloy plating layer on the surface of the steel substrate; and wherein, from the time the steel substrate is pulled out of the hot-dip plating bath to the time the surface of the hot-dip plating metal on the steel substrate reaches 300°C, the cooling rate at which the surface of the hot-dip plating metal is cooled is within the range of 5°C/sec to 100°C/sec.

